        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 8:59AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 859 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sunset, or near Marion, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wapanocca National Wildlife Refuge, Mound City, Jericho, Booker,
Griffin Corner, West Memphis, Gammon, Quito, Cunningham Corner,
Clarkedale, Woodstock, St Clair, Harvard, Locke, Dixonville,
Millington, Sloanville, Crittenden, Riceville, and Vincent.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
